body:
@fpapon Since instantiating this class when parsing the INI is a regression from 1.13.0 (it worked there) and since OSGi needs all the help it can get, I still think this should be fixed. :smile: 

(also I think that being able to pass a classloader as a parameter to code actively using a classloader, is probably a good design decision in any case)

At the same time, since this had a 1-line workaround https://github.com/apache/shiro/issues/1500#issuecomment-2151577796 it is not something I feel strongly about. :smile:

@himakar579 Thank you!  However, I am not sure what details you are looking for.
Do you have any specific question(s)?
The issue is pretty clear what needs to be done. Remove all references to quartz module.

@Himakar Any updates please?
We have created 3.x branch and can merge this if you make the necessary changes.
Thank you!
